    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rooting for WordPerfect</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Carlson letter on Joel Brinkley's Sept 21 article cites presence of Corel, maker of WordPerfect software, on Linux</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Joel Brinkley must not be familiar with Linux. Corel has established a presence there, with an office suite and a ported version of WordPerfect 8 that are even more affordable than the comparable Windows programs. These perform nearly all of the same functions, and the files are compatible across both platforms.</p>
        <p>TOM CARLSON  Lawrence, Kan.</p>
      </block>
